<item>
            <title>[SPARK-18579] spark-csv strips whitespace (pyspark) </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18579</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ignoreLeadingWhiteSpace and ignoreTrailingWhiteSpace are supported on CSV reader (and defaults to false).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However these are not supported options on the CSV writer and so the library defaults take place which strips the whitespace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it would make the most sense if the writer semantics matched the reader (and did not alter the data) however this would be a change in behaviour.  In any case it&apos;d be great to have the &lt;em&gt;option&lt;/em&gt; to strip or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
